NOTE 5RESTRUCTURING CHARGES

FISCAL 2004

RESTRUCTURING ACTIONS

THE COMPANY RECORDED TOTAL RESTRUCTURING CHARGES OF

APPROXIMATELY $23 MILLION DURING THE YEAR ENDED SEPTEMBER 25, 2004,

INCLUDING APPROXIMATELY $14 MILLION IN SEVERANCE COSTS, $5.5 MILLION IN ASSET

IMPAIRMENTS, AND A $3.5 MILLION CHARGE FOR LEASE CANCELLATIONS IN CONJUNCTION

WITH THE VACATING OF A LEASED SALES FACILITY RELATED TO A EUROPEAN WORKFORCE

REDUCTION DURING THE FOURTH QUARTER OF 2004. OF THE $23 MILLION CHARGE,

$19.7 MILLION HAD BEEN UTILIZED BY THE END OF 2005, WITH THE REMAINING $3.3

MILLION CONSISTING OF $0.7 MILLION FOR EMPLOYEE SEVERANCE BENEFITS AND $2.6

MILLION FOR LEASE CANCELLATIONS. THESE ACTIONS WILL RESULT IN THE TERMINATION

OF 461 EMPLOYEES, 448 OF WHICH HAD BEEN TERMINATED PRIOR TO THE END OF 2005.

